      <abstract obkms_id="2204f183-faea-4d09-a657-57d3a83d24de" obkms_process="TRUE">
        <label>Abstract</label>
        <p>A new species of <italic><tp:taxon-name obkms_id="792ddd71-70ef-498e-962e-f879e612398e" obkms_process="TRUE"><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Dorstenia</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> L. (<italic><tp:taxon-name obkms_id="87b6fb59-e498-4bee-9821-ecc06c992780" obkms_process="TRUE"><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Moraceae</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic>), <italic><tp:taxon-name obkms_id="a8700557-9e3a-44ed-ac53-5d78d911e173" obkms_process="TRUE"><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Dorstenia</tp:taxon-name-part><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="species">luamensis</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> M.E.Leal, is described from the Luama Wildlife Reserve, west of Lake Tanganyika and north of the town of Kalemie in the eastern part of the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC). This species is endemic to the region and differs from any of the other species by its fernlike lithophytic habit and lack of latex. A description and illustration of this species is presented here. <italic><tp:taxon-name obkms_id="4a1548a6-ee0b-4734-b1c3-3ec5fba1b4b2" obkms_process="TRUE"><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Dorstenia</tp:taxon-name-part><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="species">luamensis</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> M.E.Leal inhabits moist and shady vertical rock faces close to small waterfalls in the forest; the species is distributed in small populations within the type locality, and merits the conservation status of endangered (EN).</p>
      </abstract>
