        <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="Phenology">
          <title>Phenology.</title>
          <p>The specimens were collected in late October.</p>
        </tp:treatment-sec>
        <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="Ecology">
          <title>Ecology.</title>
          <p><italic><tp:taxon-name obkms_id="d3662057-6759-4bfd-b80c-e60400650e58" obkms_process="TRUE"><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Dorstenia</tp:taxon-name-part><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="species">luamensis</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> M.E.Leal inhabits moist and shady vertical rock faces close to small waterfalls in forest within a riverine forest-open woodland-savanna mosaic.</p>
        </tp:treatment-sec>
        <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="Distribution and conservation status">
          <title>Distribution and conservation status.</title>
          <p>The species is distributed in small populations within the type locality, and according to these demographic characteristics it merits the conservation status of endangered (EN).</p>
        </tp:treatment-sec>
        <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="Etymology">
          <title>Etymology.</title>
          <p>The epithet <italic>luamensis</italic> refers the Luama Wildlife Reserve which is drained by the Luama River.</p>
